predicted_summary: Directs the Secretary of Commerce to: (1) make an injury determination in an antidumping or countervailing duty investigation initiated under this Act; or (2) determine whether an industry in the United States is being threatened with material injury. summary_generated: Unfair Foreign Competition Act of 2007- Amends the Tariff Act of 1930 to authorize a petitioning party, within 30 days after an antidumping or countervailing duty investigation is initiated, to elect to bring a civil action in a U.S. district court for a determination that: (1) an industry in the United States is materially injured, or is threatened with material injury, by reason of imports of the merchandise subject to the investigation and that imports of the subject merchandise are not negligible; or (2) the establishment of such an industry is materially retarded, by reason of imports, or sales, for importation, of the merchandise subject to the investigation, and that imports of the subject merchandise are not negligible.
